{{!
    @template mod_jitsi/addjibri_confirm

    Confirmation page shown before adding a Jibri recording VM to an existing
    GCP Jitsi server: instructions, Prosody/Jicofo reconfiguration script with
    copy button, machine type input and confirm/cancel actions.

    Example context (json):
    {
        "hostname": "meet.example.com",
        "script": "#!/bin/bash\necho hello",
        "confirmurl": "https://example.com/mod/jitsi/servermanagement.php?action=addjibri&id=3&confirm=1&sesskey=x",
        "cancelurl": "https://example.com/mod/jitsi/servermanagement.php",
        "sesskey": "abc123"
    }
}}
<div class="alert alert-info mb-3">
    <p>This will create a dedicated Jibri recording VM alongside your existing Jitsi server.
        Two steps are required:</p>
    <ol>
        <li><strong>Run the script below on your Jitsi VM</strong>
            — reconfigures Prosody and Jicofo to accept Jibri connections.</li>
        <li><strong>Click "Confirm"</strong>
            — Moodle will create and configure the Jibri VM in GCP automatically.</li>
    </ol>
</div>

<div class="mb-4">
    <h5>Reconfiguration script for the Jitsi VM</h5>
    <p class="text-muted small"><code>ssh user@{{hostname}} 'sudo bash -s' &lt; script.sh</code></p>
    <pre id="jibri-reconfig-script" class="bg-dark text-light p-3 rounded"
        style="max-height:300px; overflow-y:auto; font-size:0.8em;">{{script}}</pre>
    <button type="button" class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-secondary mb-3" id="copy-reconfig-script">Copy script</button>
</div>

<form method="post" action="{{confirmurl}}">
    <input type="hidden" name="sesskey" value="{{sesskey}}">
    <div class="mb-4">
        <label class="form-label fw-semibold" for="jibri-machine">Jibri VM machine type</label>
        <input type="text" id="jibri-machine" name="jibrimachinetype" value="n2-standard-4" class="form-control mb-1">
        <small class="text-muted">Minimum recommended: <code>n2-standard-4</code> (4 vCPUs, 16 GB RAM).</small>
    </div>
    <div>
        <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary me-2">Confirm — Create Jibri VM</button>
        <a href="{{cancelurl}}" class="btn btn-secondary">{{#str}} cancel, core {{/str}}</a>
    </div>
</form>
